==== RBC Glutathione

Reduced glutathione is among the most replicated specific oxidative stress findings in ME/CFS, documented in both erythrocytes and brain tissue. Shungu et al.\ (2012) found significantly reduced cortical glutathione via MRS, correlating with physical functioning and energy levels, with pilot data showing NAC normalized glutathione and symptoms Clinical audits of mitochondrial support protocols in ME/CFS patients consistently identify glutathione depletion as part of the oxidative stress profile Glutathione functions both as a biomarker of oxidative burden and as a treatment target: N-acetylcysteine (NAC) is used to replenish glutathione precursors.

